# Enforce LF line endings for all text files so tooling is consistent across OSes and
# CI. In particular `prettier --check` uses endOfLine=lf; without this, CRLF-committed
# blobs fail the Format gate on Linux runners. Binary files are auto-detected and left
# untouched; a few common types are pinned explicitly for safety.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.ico binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
